Privacy Policy for Daily Budget Manager

Last updated: 18/10/2024

This Privacy Policy describes how ZeroPoint collects, uses, and shares information about you when you use the Daily Budget Manager application.

Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information when you use our App:

Personal Information:

We do not collect any personally identifiable information unless you provide it voluntarily, such as when you register or create an account.

Transaction Data:

We collect information about your transactions, including amounts, categories, payment methods, and dates. This information is used solely to provide you with budgeting features and insights.

Usage Data:

We may collect information about your usage of the App, including your interactions, the pages you visit, and the time spent on the App.

Device Information:

We may collect information about your device, including the device type, operating system, and unique device identifiers.

Cookies and Tracking Technologies:

We may use cookies and similar technologies to track your usage of the App and enhance your experience.

How We Use Your Information
We may use the information we collect for various purposes, including:

To provide, maintain, and improve our App and services.
To process and analyse your transactions.
To send you notifications and updates regarding your transactions and budgeting goals.
To provide personalized content and advertisements.
To monitor and analyse usage and trends to improve your experience.

Third-Party Services
We may use third-party services to help us operate the App and provide our services. These third parties may have access to your personal information to perform tasks on our behalf but are obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.

Advertising:
We use Google Mobile Ads to display advertisements in our App. Google may use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to our App or other websites on the Internet. For more information on how Google uses your data, please refer to Google's Privacy Policy.
Your Rights
You have certain rights regarding your personal information, including:

The right to access, update, or delete the information we have about you.
The right to object to our processing of your personal information.
The right to request that we restrict the processing of your personal information.
The right to withdraw consent at any time where we rely on your consent to process your personal information.
Children's Privacy
Our App is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete that information.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date at the top of this Privacy Policy. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us:

Email: zeropointapps@gmail.com
